# Money App Privacy Policy
Effective date: August 1, 2023

Welcome to Money App, the mobile application designed to assist you in managing your expenses and income. This Privacy Policy outlines our practices regarding the collection, use, and disclosure of your information and your rights concerning that information.

## 1. Information Collection
### Personal Data
When you sign up for a Money App account, we may collect your name, email address, and any other information you provide.

### Transaction Data
We collect information about your financial transactions, including the amounts, dates, categories, and locations of your purchases and income sources.

### Device Information
We may collect information about the device you use to access the Money App, such as the device type, operating system, and unique device identifiers.

### Location Data
If you enable location services, we may collect information about your location to provide location-based features and services.

## 2. Use of Data
The information we collect is used in various ways, including:
- To provide, maintain, and improve the Money App's core features, such as tracking your expenses, income, and budgeting
- To personalize your experience within the Money App, such as by providing customized budget recommendations or expense categories
- To send you important updates, reminders, or other communications related to the Money App
- To display relevant advertisements within the Money App
- To analyze usage patterns and user feedback to improve the Money App

## 3. Data Security and Retention
We take reasonable measures to protect your personal information from unauthorized access, use, or disclosure. We retain your information for as long as necessary to provide the Money App's services and to comply with our legal obligations.

## 4. Your Rights and Choices
You have the right to access, update, and delete your personal information. You can also choose to opt-out of certain features, such as location-based services or push notifications.

## 5. Third-Party Services
The Money App may integrate with or contain links to third-party services, such as social media platforms or payment providers. These third-party services have their own privacy policies, and we are not responsible for the privacy practices of these services.

## 6. Changes to This Privacy Policy
We may update our Privacy Policy from time to time. We will notify you of any changes by posting the updated policy within the Money App.
